# =============================================================================
# OpenForge — environment template
# =============================================================================
# Local dev:
#   cp .env.example .env          # optional baseline
#   cp .env.example .env.secret   # then put real secrets in .env.secret (gitignored)
#
# Vite loads `.env` then `.env.secret` (override). Prefer `.env.secret` for IDs/secrets.
# Restart `npm run dev` after changes.
#
# Guide: ../docs/deployment/env-secrets.md
# =============================================================================

# --- GitHub OAuth App
# In GitHub → OAuth App → "Authorization callback URL" must match redirect_uri **exactly**
# (scheme, host, port, path — no trailing slash). Common fix: use localhost consistently.
#
# Optional: force redirect URI (authorize + token exchange) regardless of browser host:
# GITHUB_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/auth/github/callback
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# --- Required for signed session cookies (openssl rand -hex 32)
AUTH_SECRET=

# --- Public vars (optional) — PUBLIC_* is exposed to the browser; never put secrets there.
# PUBLIC_APP_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173

# --- Postgres / Redis (after `deploy/compose` is up — see docs/deployment/staging-stack.md)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://openforge:YOUR_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/openforge
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
